## Test Characteristics

**Unit tests should:**
- âœ… Test a single function/method in isolation
- âœ… Use mocks for external dependencies
- âœ… Run quickly (<1ms per test)
- âœ… Be deterministic (same input = same output)
- âœ… Follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)

**Example:**
```javascript
// tests/unit/config/constants.test.js
import { formatDuration } from '../../../src/config/constants.js';

describe('formatDuration', () => {
    it('formats milliseconds to human-readable string', () => {
        expect(formatDuration(1000)).toBe('1s');
        expect(formatDuration(60000)).toBe('1m');
        expect(formatDuration(3600000)).toBe('1h');
    });
});
```

## Migration Plan

To migrate existing unit tests:
```bash
# Move API client tests
mv tests/apiClient.test.js tests/unit/services/

# Move pure function tests
mv tests/test_apiClient_pure_functions.js tests/unit/services/

# Update imports in moved files
# Change: import { ... } from '../src/...'
# To:     import { ... } from '../../../src/...'
```

## Running Unit Tests

```bash
# Run all unit tests
npm run test:unit

# Run with coverage
npm run test:unit:coverage

# Watch mode
npm run test:unit:watch
```

